From 6f5d93ffec197e54acbfd1eb65b32cb56976dea9 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>
Date: Thu, 8 Jan 2026 01:16:56 +0100
Subject: [PATCH 1/8] arm: gxp: add device tree overlay support via configfs

Add device tree overlay support enabling runtime loading of device tree
overlays through the configfs interface. This allows platform-specific
hardware configurations to be applied at boot time based on server ID.

Key changes:
- Add configfs interface for overlay management
- Add sysfs interface for overlay status
- Support for of_overlay_disable kernel parameter
- Extend overlay support with proper target node resolution

This is required for HPE GXP BMC platforms where different ProLiant
server variants need different device tree configurations loaded at
runtime.

Signed-off-by: Marcello Sylvester Bauer <marcello.bauer@9elements.com>

